sentences: Assala Mostafa Hatem Nasri (Arabic: أصالة مصطفى حاتم نصري; born 15 May 1969), commonly known as Assala (Arabic: أصالة), is a Syrian musical artist.
Assala began her musical career by performing patriotic, religious, and children's songs when she was four years old.
In 1984, Mostafa Nasri died after suffering from internal bleeding caused by a car accident.
Assala's commercial musical career debuted in 1991 with the Egyptian song hit Law Ta'rafou (Egyptian Arabic: لو تعرفو).
Ever since the beginning of the Syrian Civil War, in 2011, Assala Nasri claimed her support for the Syrian people and her commitment against Bashar al Assad.
She had her first composing experience in the writing of one song, released in 2011.
For her commitment in the conflict, Assala sang at the International Peace day as a new ambassador for "Peace Building Through Music."
